+ * material lookup: of the 12 "grid*"-named objects, only TWO are genuine
+ * full-frame backdrop art -- "grid5" (bound texture "back_ex", the day/
+ * night split panel with balloons/stars baked into one texture) and
+ * "grid14" (bound texture "back_house", the town-silhouette strip, same
+ * footprint squashed to a short horizontal band). Every other "grid*"
+ * object and "hikari" is a separate sub-object with its own dedicated
+ * vertex buffer and texture (confetti/glow-ray atlases, a light-glint
+ * sprite) and must NOT stretch. Most notably, "grid3" -- previously
+ * matched and stretched by the old prefix rule -- resolves to bound
+ * texture "mario_ex": it is Mario's own hero-pose graphic, merely named
+ * with a "grid" prefix as an authoring artifact, not a backdrop role
+ * indicator. That misclassification was the actual, confirmed cause of a
+ * previously reported "Mario looks stretched" bug. Now matched by exact
+ * name only ("grid5"/"grid14"); everything else in this model is left
+ * completely untouched.
+ *
+ * The predicate that used to sit here, feeding a selective horizontal
+ * stretch of those two objects, is removed -- the stretch call is gone
+ * (see BootTitleCreate's own call-site comment below) in favor of a
+ * mirror-extend that keeps their native vertices. The per-object analysis
+ * above still stands as the reason grid5/grid14, and only those two, get
+ * any widescreen treatment at all. */
+
